import random

# Predefined ranges and distributions for each feature
target_material = ['plastic', 'aluminium', 'gold', 'polypropylene']
target_thickness = [0.25, 1.5, 4.0, 0.3, 0.8, 1.2, 6.0, 7.5, 0.1, 5.6, 2.9, 0.7, 1.1, 3.2, 0.6, 4.9, 1.9, 5.8, 2.5, 0.9]
pulse_width = [150, 320, 580, 760, 1100, 1350, 2100, 2460, 460, 870, 1650, 2310, 2940, 3470, 3850, 5560, 6780, 8320, 11950, 15700]
energy = [3.1, 11.4, 6.7, 1.8, 10.1, 5.9, 12.3, 7.6, 8.8, 2.2, 4.5, 15.2, 9.0, 7.1, 11.8, 4.9, 16.5, 12.9, 7.9, 13.5]
spot_size = [2.7, 4.1, 3.6, 5.5, 3.2, 4.8, 3.0, 6.2, 3.7, 4.5, 4.2, 5.9, 3.4, 4.0, 5.1, 2.9, 4.6, 3.8, 5.3, 3.1]
intensity = [5.2e20, 8.1e20, 6.9e20, 3.7e20, 7.5e20, 9.2e20, 4.8e20, 6.1e20, 2.5e21, 1.1e21, 6.4e20, 8.3e20, 5.5e20, 7.9e20, 3.9e21, 1.2e21, 6.7e20, 1.5e21, 4.4e20, 2.8e21]
power = [2.1e13, 5.6e13, 8.9e13, 3.5e13, 7.2e13, 1.3e14, 1.2e13, 1.8e14, 9.5e13, 6.3e13, 4.4e13, 2.3e14, 1.1e14, 1.7e14, 3.2e14, 2.9e14, 8.8e13, 1.6e14, 5.3e13, 1.0e14]
cutoff_energy = [6.2, 10.7, 5.1, 9.2, 7.8, 4.3, 11.1, 8.5, 5.5, 12.6, 3.9, 11.5, 7.3, 4.6, 10.4, 6.9, 12.2, 9.8, 8.1, 6.7]

# Generate 25 new data points
data_points = []
for _ in range(25):
    target_material_index = random.randint(0, len(target_material) - 1)
    target_thickness_value = random.uniform(min(target_thickness), max(target_thickness))
    pulse_width_value = random.choice(pulse_width)
    energy_value = random.choice(energy)
    spot_size_value = random.choice(spot_size)
    intensity_value = random.uniform(*intensity[int(random.randint(0, len(intensity)-1))].shape)
    power_value = random.uniform(*power[int(random.randint(0, len(power)-1))].shape)
    cutoff_energy_value = random.choice(cutoff_energy)
    
    data_points.append([target_material[target_material_index], target_thickness_value, pulse_width_value, energy_value, spot_size_value, intensity_value, power_value, cutoff_energy_value])

# Print 25 generated samples inside an array
print(data_points)
